HEADWORD: Acatalepsy
<hw>A*cat"a*lep`sy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ to seize, comprehend.]</ety>
<def>Incomprehensibility of things; the doctrine held by the ancient
Skeptic philosophers, that human knowledge never amounts to certainty,
but only to probability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acataleptic</ent>⟦br⟧
